

--- ssh-keygen
and copy content from id_rsa.pub file and paste into github/gitlab ssh keys section

ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"
Replace "your_email@example.com" with the email you use on GitHub.

If your system doesn’t support ed25519, use:
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "your_email@example.com"
You’ll see output like:


Copy code
Enter file in which to save the key (/home/youruser/.ssh/id_ed25519):
Press Enter to accept the default location.

If asked for a passphrase, you can enter one (recommended) or leave it empty.

2. eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"
3. ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
4. cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
5. Go to GitHub → Settings → SSH and GPG keys
